241
00:21:53,600 --> 00:22:02,040
Trying to drive culture change is both one of the 
most challenging things and rewarding things. For  

242
00:22:02,040 --> 00:22:07,720
the first year of my role ... There was a chapter 
of my time at Twitter, maybe just to backup,  

243
00:22:07,720 --> 00:22:12,480
that was just leading Periscope. In that first 
chapter of maybe two years, I was not really  

244
00:22:12,480 --> 00:22:17,400
involved with Twitter stuff all that much. 
That started to change when we really tried  

245
00:22:17,400 --> 00:22:22,320
integrating Periscope with Twitter, but chapter 
two of my time at Twitter was when I became the  

246
00:22:22,320 --> 00:22:28,760
head of product. That first year of being the 
head of product was one of the most difficult of  

247
00:22:28,760 --> 00:22:35,160
my career not because the work was difficult, but 
because it was so politically and bureaucratically  

248
00:22:35,160 --> 00:22:40,680
exhausting to try and change culture in a 
