00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:39,600
we got acquired by a big, public, ad tech 
company called Blackboard, and we were 19  

259
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:44,600
at the time. We got thrown into a public ... 
I was a senior executive at a public company  

260
00:23:44,600 --> 00:23:50,440
that was not your quintessential tech company. It 
was even more difficult to get things done. So,  

261
00:23:50,440 --> 00:23:54,760
through the four years I spent there, 
I learned a lot about how to navigate  

262
00:23:54,760 --> 00:23:58,080
that type of environment.
It all came coming back  

263
00:23:58,840 --> 00:24:01,771
when I was given the product role at Twitter. 
That first year of changing culture was like-

264
00:24:01,771 --> 00:24:06,920
... product role at Twitter. That first year of 
changing culture was like walking through mud,  

265
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:15,320
and it was really difficult. But I think when 
we started building that alignment and building  

266
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:20,680
excitement that like, oh, actually maybe we 
should be taking some bigger swings, and when  

267
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:27,920
