again is because they refined the core. This is  

284
00:26:04,120 --> 00:26:09,720
when they went from the reverse chronological 
timeline to the ranked timeline, and the year  

285
00:26:09,720 --> 00:26:13,520
after that was a lot of knob turning. It was like, 
how do we make these recommendations better? How  

286
00:26:13,520 --> 00:26:18,760
do we make our push notifications more relevant?
Now, that is not an inspiring product strategy.  

287
00:26:18,760 --> 00:26:23,640
That does not result in the product feeling 
materially different or adding new capabilities,  

288
00:26:23,640 --> 00:26:31,480
but it did return the company to user growth. 
And I think that the fact that it did actually  

289
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:38,120
calcified the organization's reticence to 
take any risky bets even more. So it was a  

290
00:26:38,120 --> 00:26:45,920
very interesting predicament because when I 
got into the role, the goal wasn't to change  

291
00:26:45,920 --> 00:26:50,320
