actually not that hard to do if you're a user of  

312
00:28:36,880 --> 00:28:43,680
Twitter and you can think critically. It was ripe 
with opportunity. And so it was actually really  

313
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:50,280
fun and amazing to be able to craft a plan that 
started to take a swing at some of these things. 

314
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:54,920
And the other thing I'll add to this is that 
there were so many sacred cows at Twitter that  

315
00:28:54,920 --> 00:28:59,200
the sacred cows are their own roadmap. It's like a 
built-in free roadmap of like, all right, what are  

316
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:05,600
all the things that you think we're not allowed to 
change? Let's start there. Everything from moving  

317
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:10,880
from reverse chron to a ranked feed, that was 
a sacred cow. Text and 140 characters, that's a  

318
00:29:10,880 --> 00:29:17,480
sacred cow. Not letting anyone control any tweets 
that they see on the platform. The notion of Lenny  

319
00:29:17,480 --> 00:29:24,080
owning his reply space was anathema at Twitter.
It's just like if a tweet gets, if you get an  

320
00:29:24,080 --> 00:29:30,240
at mention and you don't like it or it's abusive, 
