321
00:29:30,240 --> 00:29:36,200
with [inaudible 00:29:30], all that stuff, 
those are all sacred cows. And the process  

322
00:29:36,200 --> 00:29:42,680
of starting to address those one by one reveals 
a lot of the cultural hesitations that existed. 

323
00:29:43,880 --> 00:29:49,080
So yeah, I'll never forget one of the first 
features, and this is such a tiny feature  

324
00:29:49,080 --> 00:29:55,720
that we worked on after I started the role, 
we were building this feature called hide  

325
00:29:55,720 --> 00:29:59,960
replies. It still exists in the product today. 
If someone replies to one of your tweets,  

326
00:29:59,960 --> 00:30:04,760
in the tweet details area as a reply to one of 
your conversations, before you had no ability,  

327
00:30:04,760 --> 00:30:10,600
the only way you could address unwanted content 
was reporting it. So that was like Twitter  

328
00:30:10,600 --> 00:30:15,760
acting as policemen and policewoman, completely 
unscalable and challenging, especially in the  

329
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:20,760
context of someone replying to one of your tweets.
And so we wanted to add a feature that let you  

330
00:30:20,760 --> 00:30:25,120
hide a reply to one of your tweets, and it's not 
impacting what people say. It's not impacting free  

331
00:30:25,120 --> 00:30:28,760
speech in the sense of you can still broadcast 
whatever you want, but if you're going to come  

332
00:30:28,760 --> 00:30:34,280
into my reply space and say some shit that I 
don't want to see in my feed, I should be able  

333
00:30:34,280 --> 00:30:40,040
to hide that. Tweet what you want, but don't at 
mention. You can't scream in my face basically. 

334
00:30:40,040 --> 00:30:47,080
And I remember we had a PM on our team who 
was leading this feature who a few weeks  

335
00:30:47,080 --> 00:30:52,240
into this project mentioned to me that she 
had had a conversation with someone on the  

336
00:30:52,240 --> 00:30:58,160
engineering team that told them, "Don't work 
on this feature. This is bad for your career.  

337
00:30:58,160 --> 00:31:02,360
This is not going to launch, and you don't want 
to work on this. You don't want to be seen as  

338
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:09,520
having worked on this." Because it was so kind 
of anathema to we can't let people hide replies  

339
00:31:09,520 --> 00:31:17,320
