something's got to change. Assuming the person  

598
00:53:52,440 --> 00:53:56,440
who's making this assessment has good product 
taste, which is in of itself subjective obviously,  

599
00:53:57,320 --> 00:54:04,160
but my personal view on this would be in the 
role that I had, if I saw that our organization  

600
00:54:04,160 --> 00:54:10,280
was being incentivized to make decisions that 
to some non-trivial degree of the time were  

601
00:54:10,280 --> 00:54:17,160
just bad decisions that I don't like as a 
user, I can't stand by as a user or builder,  

602
00:54:17,160 --> 00:54:20,960
then something's got to change. Either bad 
judgment was made in following the process or  

603
00:54:20,960 --> 00:54:26,360
the process was wrong, or if that framework, 
it didn't even lead to the right debates,  

604
00:54:26,880 --> 00:54:33,400
then that's how you know. Either you have 
an incentive problem but the team did what  

605
00:54:33,400 --> 00:54:38,560
they were incentivized to do or that there was bad 
judgment and that's a different problem obviously. 

606
00:54:38,560 --> 00:54:44,860
But I think in the situation we found ourselves 
in where the team was again understandably hyper  

607
00:54:44,860 --> 00:54:50,040
focused on driving DAU because that was the 
strategy for so long. It left so little room for  

608
00:54:50,040 --> 00:54:56,320
even taking ambitious bets that in the short term 
wouldn't drive DAU, like some of our bets that  

609
00:54:56,880 --> 00:55:02,560
I still to this day believe in hurt DAU in the 
