688
01:02:02,720 --> 01:02:07,280
We blew up in the US, we then blew up in France. 
We then blew up in Turkey. We then blew up in the  

689
01:02:07,280 --> 01:02:12,840
Middle East and you had these incredible surges, 
but underneath that surge, the core product had  

690
01:02:12,840 --> 01:02:19,040
retention issues and we ultimately just did 
not, we didn't spend enough time prioritizing,  

691
01:02:19,040 --> 01:02:24,680
addressing those. And in fact, we shipped product 
changes that made those retention issues worse.  

692
01:02:24,680 --> 01:02:28,800
Compounding that was the fact that one of the 
theses behind our acquisition, the Twitter  

693
01:02:28,800 --> 01:02:32,960
acquisition, was that we would leverage the scale 
and the community and the product mechanics of  

694
01:02:32,960 --> 01:02:39,520
Twitter to make the product grow faster and also 
become more durable. And I think that's connects  

695
01:02:39,520 --> 01:02:43,280
to one of the reasons why I feel like one of 
my learnings and one of the things that we knew  

696
01:02:43,280 --> 01:02:50,800
but just failed to execute on was that I still 
am very skeptical that there can be a consumer  

697
01:02:50,800 --> 01:02:56,920
